This module helps in identifying attack surfaces for vulnerability testing.

(iii) sqli_scanner.py
This file detects SQL Injection vulnerabilities.
Purpose
It attempts to inject SQL payloads into discovered input fields and checks if the application is vulnerable.
What It Does
Takes form data from crawler.


Inserts SQL payloads such as:
 ' OR '1'='1
Submits modified request.
Analyzes server response for:
SQL syntax errors


Authentication bypass


Abnormal database behavior


If database errors appear, it confirms SQL Injection vulnerability.

(iv) xss_scanner.py
This file detects Cross-Site Scripting vulnerabilities.
Purpose
It injects JavaScript payloads into input fields and checks whether they are reflected in the response.
What It Does
Receives forms from crawler.


Injects payload:
 <script>alert('XSS')</script>
Submits form.
Checks if script appears in response unescaped.


If payload is reflected in page source, XSS is confirmed.


